<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1341] TProtocol.h endian detection wrong with boost</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1341</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When compiling on platforms without /usr/include/endian.h (e.g. Windows.h), TProtocol.h uses boost to detect the endianess, but does it wrong: boost&apos;s endian.hpp will only #define BOOST_LITTLE_ENDIAN with no value (unlike endian.h)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached is a patch against trunk which fixes the code that uses boost. Tested on Windows, boost 1.44.0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
